From 027da806b2fc34612cc8c5e78b2c4fa519d62085 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matthias Petermann <mp@petermann-it.de>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 07:30:01 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] cells: introduce v3 control plane cellman / libcellman with
 Lua DSL

Replace the shell-based v2 orchestration layer with the v3 stack built
around cellman and shared libcellman APIs, consumed consistently by CLI
and cellui. Integrate this control plane cleanly with secmodel_cell and
cellctl as the low-level kernel/runtime boundary.

Move desired state to declarative /etc/cellman/*.lua files with
deterministic load order, typed IR parsing, and explicit apply-based
convergence semantics, while keeping read/output contracts stable for
automation.

Preserve operational capabilities (lifecycle, autostart, storage, and
backups) and harden safety defaults with fail-closed validation, strict
mount/path guards, host-mount opt-in gating, and explicit confirmation
for destructive operations.
