-NetBSD cells-v2 specification (unified control plane)
-=====================================================
-
-Status
-------
-This document reflects the current implementation in this tree:
-- `secmodel_cell` (kernel isolation/policy + snapshot telemetry)
-- `cellctl` (sysctl-facing control/metrics adapter)
-- `cellmgr` (desired + runtime + backup orchestration)
-- `cellui` (interactive TUI over `cellmgr`)
-
-
-1. System model
----------------
-Cells-v2 is a layered control plane:
-
-    +------------------------------+
-    | cellui (curses TUI)          |
-    +---------------+--------------+
-                    |
-    +---------------v--------------+
-    | cellmgr                       |
-    | - desired manifests           |
-    | - runtime rendering           |
-    | - reconcile/apply engine      |
-    | - backup/restore              |
-    | - ipc serve (stdio protocol)  |
-    +---------------+--------------+
-                    |
-    +---------------v--------------+
-    | cellctl                       |
-    | - create/destroy/exec         |
-    | - supervise wrapper           |
-    | - list/stats snapshots        |
-    +---------------+--------------+
-                    |
-    +---------------v--------------+
-    | secmodel_cell (kernel)        |
-    | security.models.cell.* sysctl |
-    +------------------------------+
-
-Conceptual domains:
-- Desired state: authoritative manifests (`*.cell`, `*.apply`, `*.volume`)
-- Runtime state: rendered cell trees, mounts, live kernel cell instances
-- Reconciliation: `cellmgr apply` converges runtime to desired
-
-
-2. `cellmgr` command surface
-----------------------------
-Top-level commands:
-- `system` (`bootstrap`, `reset`)
-- `ipc` (`serve --stdio`)
-- `cell` (`list|show|fields|create|set|remove|start|stop|restart|shell|plan|edit|backup`)
-- `volume` (`list|show|fields|create|set|remove|backup`)
-- `apply`
-
-Read contract (`cell` + `volume`):
-- default output: human-readable table
-- `-T`: stable TSV output
-- `-H`: suppress TSV header (`-T` required)
-- `--view merged|desired|runtime`
-- `-o field1,field2,...` projection in caller-defined order
-
-Mutation scope contract:
-- `desired`: manifests only
-- `runtime`: live/rendered state only
-- `both`: desired + runtime effect
-
-Scope restrictions by command family:
-- `cell create|set`: `desired|both`
-- `cell start|stop|restart`: `runtime|both`
-- `cell remove`: `desired|runtime|both`
-- `volume create|set`: `desired|both`
-- `volume remove`: `desired|runtime|both`
-
-
-3. State and storage layout
----------------------------
-Default layout:
-
-    /etc/cellmgr/
-      <name>.cell      (desired cell manifest)
-      <name>.apply     (declarative apply plan)
-      <name>.volume    (desired volume manifest)
-
-    /var/cellmgr/
-      base/<release>-<arch>/
-      releases/<release>/<arch>/{base,etc[,xbase]}.tar.xz
-      cells/<name>/
-        cell.conf
-        root/
-        .overlay/      (legacy fallback: overlay/)
-        state/
-          manifest.sha256
-          apply.sha256
-          last_reconcile_epoch
-          last_reconcile_result
-      volumes/<name>/
-
-    /var/backups/cellmgr/
-      volumes/<name>_YYYYmmddHHMMSS.tar.gz
-      overlays/<name>_YYYYmmddHHMMSS.tar.gz
-
-Runtime overlay model:
-- shared base is mounted read-only at `<root>`
-- per-cell writable layer is mounted at `<root>/.overlay`
-- base paths `/etc`, `/var`, `/tmp`, `/home`, `/root`, `/usr/pkg`, `/opt` are symlinked
-  into `/.overlay`
-
-
-4. Manifest contracts
----------------------
-Cell manifest (`<name>.cell`) keys:
-- `CELL_NAME`
-- `CELL_AUTOSTART` (`YES|NO`)
-- `CELL_CREATE_PROFILE` (`low|medium|high`, default in create path: `high`)
-- `CELL_CREATE_RESERVED_PORTS` (comma-separated ports)
-- `CELL_CREATE_RLIMIT_NOFILE` (integer or `unlimited`)
-- `CELL_CREATE_RLIMIT_AS` (integer or `unlimited`)
-- `CELL_CREATE_RLIMIT_CORE` (integer or `unlimited`)
-- `CELL_SUPERVISE_FACILITY`
-- `CELL_SUPERVISE_STDOUT_LEVEL`
-- `CELL_SUPERVISE_STDERR_LEVEL`
-- `CELL_SUPERVISE_TAG`
-- `CELL_SUPERVISE_CMD` (required)
-- `CELL_SUPERVISE_RUN_AS` (`host:user[:group]`, `cell:user[:group]`, or `uid:uid[:gid]`)
-- `CELL_DEPENDS_ON` (comma-separated cell names)
-- `CELL_HEALTHCHECK_CMD`
-- `CELL_VOLUME_MOUNTS` (`<volume>:<target>[:ro|rw]`, normalized to explicit mode)
-
-Runtime-only derived `cell.conf` keys (written by `cellmgr apply`):
-- `CELL_SUPERVISE_RUN_UID`
-- `CELL_SUPERVISE_RUN_GID`
-- `CELL_SUPERVISE_RUN_GROUPS` (comma-separated gids)
-
-Apply plan (`<name>.apply`) directives:
-- `PKG <package>...`
-- `EXEC <command>`
-- `DIR <path> [mode=...] [owner=...] [group=...]`
-- `LINE <path> | <text>`
-- `SYMLINK <target> <linkpath>`
-- `COPY <host-source> <target> [mode=...] [owner=...] [group=...]`
-- `UNTAR <host-archive.tar.gz> <target-dir> [strip=n]`
-- `FILE_BEGIN <path> [mode=...] [owner=...] [group=...]` ... `FILE_END`
-- `PATCH_BEGIN <path> [strip=n]` ... `PATCH_END`
-
-Plan parser rules:
-- directives must be uppercase
-- blank lines and `#...` comments are ignored
-- `FILE_BEGIN`/`PATCH_BEGIN` targets must be absolute paths
-- `UNTAR` target must be an absolute path
-- `COPY`/`UNTAR` host sources may be absolute or relative to the apply file directory
-- `COPY`/`UNTAR` source content is folded into apply hashing for drift detection
-
-Volume manifest (`<name>.volume`) keys:
-- `VOLUME_NAME`
-- `VOLUME_MODE` (octal mode, optional)
-
-
-5. Cell read model contract
----------------------------
-Merged row superset (stable field names):
-- `name`
-- `running`
-- `desired_state`
-- `cid`
-- `refs`
-- `procs`
-- `cpu1s`
-- `cpu10s`
-- `memory`
-- `age`
-- `root`
-- `autostart`
-- `create_profile`
-- `create_reserved_ports`
-- `create_rlimit_nofile`
-- `create_rlimit_as`
-- `create_rlimit_core`
-- `depends_on`
-- `healthcheck`
-- `supervise_cmd`
-- `supervise_run_as`
-- `volume_mounts`
-- `manifest`
-- `rendered`
-- `apply_present`
-
-View restrictions:
-- `desired`: desired-centric subset
-- `runtime`: runtime-centric subset
-- `merged`: full union
-
-Snapshot assembly inputs:
-- desired manifests in `MANIFEST_DIR`
-- rendered runtime `cell.conf` in `CELL_DATA_DIR`
-- `cellctl list -T`
-- `cellctl stats -T`
-
-Schema handling details:
-- `cellctl list -T` header must be either:
-  - `CID NAME REFS PROCS AGE ROOT`, or
-  - `CID NAME REFS PROCS AGE ROOT NOFILE AS CORE`
-- `cellctl stats -T` header must be exactly:
-  - `CID NAME CPU1S CPU10S PROCS REFS MEMORY AGE ROOT`
-- schema mismatch is a hard failure
-
-Formatting rules:
-- TSV emits raw values; boolean fields are `1|0`
-- human table converts booleans to `YES|NO`
-- `age` is raw seconds in TSV, humanized in table output
-- rlimit fields are normalized to decimal integers or `unlimited`
-
-
-6. Volume read model contract
------------------------------
-Merged row superset:
-- `name`
-- `manifest`
-- `runtime`
-- `mode`
-- `path`
-- `mounted`
-- `refs`
-- `used_by`
-
-View restrictions:
-- `desired`: `name,manifest,mode,refs,used_by`
-- `runtime`: `name,runtime,path,mounted,refs,used_by`
-- `merged`: full union
-
-Value semantics:
-- `refs`: number of cell manifests referencing the volume
-- `used_by`: comma-separated referencing cell names
-- `mounted`: host mount-table probe for `<volume path>`
-
-
-7. Reconciliation contract (`cellmgr apply`)
---------------------------------------------
-Invocation:
-- `cellmgr apply [--all|<name>...] [--dry-run] [--reapply] [--restart-changed] [--silent|-v]`
-
-High-level pipeline:
-- resolve dependency order from `CELL_DEPENDS_ON`
-- reconcile volumes first
-- reconcile cells in dependency order
-- run optional plan and healthcheck phases
-
-Cell reconcile behavior summary:
-- create/update runtime `cell.conf` when manifest drift exists
-- enforce autostart intent (`start`/`stop`)
-- restart service when supervise config changed
-- resolve `CELL_SUPERVISE_RUN_AS` to runtime numeric uid/gid/groups (host
-  identities on host, cell identities from cell passwd/group databases) and render
-  resolved values into runtime `cell.conf`; treat resolved drift as service drift
-- policy-only drift (`profile/ports/rlimits`):
-  - warning by default
-  - restart only with `--restart-changed`
-- run `<name>.apply` when apply hash drift is detected or `--reapply` is set
-- when applying against running autostart cells:
-  - quiesce supervised service
-  - run plan
-  - start/restart service
-- when autostart is `NO`, plan apply uses ephemeral start/stop
-- run `CELL_HEALTHCHECK_CMD` after convergence for autostarted cells
-
-Exit status:
-- `0`: converged / success
-- `1`: error
-- `2`: `--dry-run` detected drift
-
-
-8. Backup and restore contract
-------------------------------
-Volume backup commands:
-- `volume backup create|list|restore|delete`
-
-Cell overlay backup commands:
-- `cell backup create|list|restore|delete`
-
-Behavior notes:
-- backups are timestamped `.tar.gz` archives
-- restore/delete paths are safety-checked against allowed backup roots
-- restore/delete require confirmation (or `--yes`)
-- volume restore is refused while mounted
-- overlay backup/restore is refused while cell is running or overlay is mounted
-- `--manifest` on restore restores snapshot sidecars when available
-
-
-9. IPC protocol contract
-------------------------
-Endpoint:
-- `cellmgr ipc serve --stdio`
-
-Frame format:
-- ASCII header line: `M 1 <TYPE> <ID> <P1> <P2> <P3> <LEN>\n`
-- followed by exactly `LEN` payload bytes
-
-Message types:
-- `HELLO` handshake
-- `CALL` execute command (`P1` mode: `0` capture, `1` interactive)
-- `RET` command result (`P1` rc, `P2` stdout bytes, `P3` stderr bytes)
-- `ERR` protocol/server error
-- `PING`/`PONG` keepalive
-- `BYE` shutdown
-
-Limits:
-- maximum payload: 64 MiB
-
-
-10. Validation and safety model
--------------------------------
-Name policy:
-- cell and volume names must match `[A-Za-z0-9._-]`
-
-Volume mount spec policy:
-- format: `<volume>:<abs-target>[:ro|rw]`
-- target must be absolute
-- forbidden targets: `/`, `/dev`, `/dev/*`, `/.overlay`, `/.overlay/*`
-- overlapping targets are rejected
-
-Destructive confirmation policy:
-- destructive `--all` / `--orphans` paths require interactive confirmation
-- in non-interactive contexts use `--yes`
-
-Additional guardrails:
-- `volume remove` is blocked while still referenced by manifests
-- backup delete validates expected archive naming
-- restore targets must remain under approved runtime roots
-
-
-11. `cellui` integration contract
----------------------------------
-Cell feed command (fixed order, strict parser):
-- `cellmgr cell list --view merged -T -H -o name,cid,refs,procs,root,autostart,create_profile,create_reserved_ports,create_rlimit_nofile,create_rlimit_as,create_rlimit_core,supervise_cmd,cpu1s,cpu10s,memory,age,running,manifest`
-
-Storage feed commands:
-- `cellmgr volume list --view merged -T -H -o name,manifest,runtime,mounted,refs,mode,path,used_by`
-- overlay rows derived from `cellmgr cell list --view merged -T -H -o name,manifest,running,root`
-
-Backup inventory commands:
-- `cellmgr volume backup list <name> -T -H`
-- `cellmgr cell backup list <name> -T -H`
-
-Robustness behavior:
-- command/schema failures are surfaced as refresh errors
-- malformed TSV rows are parsed with fixed-field checks and currently skipped
-- UI prefers persistent IPC; on disconnect it exposes reconnect/quit flow
