-# cellmgr examples (unified CLI)
-
-`cellmgr` uses a flat desired-state directory:
-
-- `/etc/cellmgr/<name>.cell`
-- `/etc/cellmgr/<name>.apply`
-- `/etc/cellmgr/<name>.volume`
-
-Runtime state is rendered under:
-
-- `/var/cellmgr/cells/<name>/...`
-- `/var/cellmgr/volumes/<name>`
-
-
-## Core workflow
-
-1) Bootstrap system prerequisites:
-
-```sh
-/usr/sbin/cellmgr system bootstrap
-```
-
-Use `--xbase` when your workloads require files from `xbase.tar.xz`:
-
-```sh
-/usr/sbin/cellmgr system bootstrap --xbase
-```
-
-2) Create desired manifests:
-
-```sh
-/usr/sbin/cellmgr cell create demo-edge-httpd \
-  --autostart YES \
-  --profile medium \
-  --reserved-ports 8080 \
-  --rlimit-nofile 4096 \
-  --rlimit-as 1073741824 \
-  --rlimit-core 0 \
-  --cmd '/usr/libexec/httpd -I 8080 -X -f -s /var/www/demo-edge-httpd'
-```
-
-3) Edit generated `*.cell` / `*.apply` files as needed.
-
-4) Reconcile desired to runtime:
-
-```sh
-/usr/sbin/cellmgr apply --dry-run --all
-/usr/sbin/cellmgr apply --all
-```
-
-
-## Unified read API
-
-Human table:
-
-```sh
-/usr/sbin/cellmgr cell list --view merged
-/usr/sbin/cellmgr volume list --view merged
-```
-
-Machine TSV:
-
-```sh
-/usr/sbin/cellmgr cell list --view merged -T -H -o name,cid,refs,procs,running,manifest
-/usr/sbin/cellmgr volume list --view merged -T
-```
-
-
-## Desired vs runtime scope
-
-Mutating commands accept `--scope`:
-
-- `desired` (default for create/set/remove)
-- `runtime`
-- `both`
-
-Examples:
-
-```sh
-# desired only
-/usr/sbin/cellmgr cell set demo-edge-httpd --autostart NO --scope desired
-
-# runtime only
-/usr/sbin/cellmgr cell stop demo-edge-httpd --scope runtime
-
-# desired + runtime
-/usr/sbin/cellmgr cell start demo-edge-httpd --scope both
-```
-
-
-## Volume examples
-
-Create desired volume and materialize runtime path immediately:
-
-```sh
-/usr/sbin/cellmgr volume create demo-webroot -m 0755 --scope both
-```
-
-Attach in a cell manifest:
-
-```sh
-CELL_VOLUME_MOUNTS="demo-webroot:/var/www/demo:rw"
-```
-
-`<volume|/host/path>:<target>[:ro|rw]` is required per entry.
-Host-path sources require `CELL_ALLOW_HOST_MOUNTS=YES` in `/etc/cellmgr.conf`.
-
-
-## Example stacks in this directory
-
-The following example trees are shipped:
-
-- `httpd/`
-- `mantisbt/`
-- `api-gateway/`
-- `blue-green/`
-- `php-api/`
-- `luanti/`
-- `forgejo/`
-
-Copy example manifests into `/etc/cellmgr` and run:
-
-```sh
-/usr/sbin/cellmgr apply --dry-run --all
-/usr/sbin/cellmgr apply --all
-```
-
-
-## Apply plan directives
-
-`<name>.apply` supports:
-
-- `PKG <package>`
-- `EXEC <command>`
-- `DIR <path> [mode=0755] [owner=user|@run_uid] [group=group|@run_gid]`
-- `LINE <path> | <text>`
-- `SYMLINK <target> <linkpath>`
-- `COPY <host-source> <target> [mode=0644] [owner=user|@run_uid] [group=group|@run_gid]`
-- `UNTAR <host-archive.tar.gz> <target-dir> [strip=0]`
-- `FILE_BEGIN <path> [mode=0644] [owner=user|@run_uid] [group=group|@run_gid]`
-- `FILE_END`
-- `PATCH_BEGIN <path> [strip=0]`
-- `PATCH_END`
-
-`DIR`, `COPY`, and `FILE_BEGIN` accept `owner=@run_uid` and
-`group=@run_gid` placeholders. These resolve from
-`CELL_SUPERVISE_RUN_AS` into rendered runtime `CELL_SUPERVISE_RUN_UID/GID`.
-Run-as specs support `host:user[:group]`, `cell:user[:group]`, and
-`uid:uid[:gid]` formats.
-
-`EXEC` directives run with `CELLMGR_RUN_UID`, `CELLMGR_RUN_GID`, and
-`CELLMGR_RUN_GROUPS` exported in the cell shell.
-
-Before executing each plan, `cellmgr` runs `certctl rehash` inside the target
-cell and exports `PKG_PATH` for package operations.
-For `COPY` and `UNTAR`, host source paths may be absolute or relative to the
-`<name>.apply` directory.
-Host source content is part of the apply hash, so changing a referenced file
-triggers apply without `--reapply`.
-
-
-## Operational notes
-
-- Keep `/etc/cellmgr` under version control.
-- Prefer one supervised service per cell.
-- `--all` / `--orphans` destructive removals require confirmation or `--yes`.
-- `CELL_DEPENDS_ON` defines reconcile order and rejects dependency cycles.
